rComments: His lectures can be long and dull, but are usually interesting. The midterm and final exam are basically identical and not too difficult, but a good grade really depends on how good you are at taking notes. The essay is long (12-15 p) and requires a lot of work and effort. His emails can seem condescending at times, but helpful nonetheless.

Lectures consisted of five page powerpoint slides with no information as you listen to him go on for an hour and fifty minutes. Its hard to make WW1 boring but he was very successful in doing so. Essays are incredibly hard for no reason, grades tough just because he can and definitely looks down on students.

This guy clearly doesn't care about teaching students. Lectures are dull and mind-numbing, as in 1 hour long with only four pictures and nothing else. Tries to make essays harder then they need to be. Save yourself some unnecessary anxiety and don't take him.
I have never felt so overwhelmed by a course in my 4 years of university. i am extremely relieved that this course is over. would absolutely not repeat

avoid. very difficult grader and expects a lot from students! In total, I've written 38 pages total for this class, (midterm, term paper, final) which i think is incredibly high. compared to all my other profs, especially in history, this is not normal and is far too much. he is also very snarky and unpleasant in emails.
How this professor was granted tenure is beyond me. He is one of the rudest and most condescending profs I've ever met at this university.
By far the rudest and most unprofessional professor I've ever had in my three years at uOttawa. Avoid this guy at all costs.
i was fooled by the earlier good ratings. this prof is very tough and demanding in terms of work load. not personable and his emails are RUDE
so rude. very unhelpful. do NOT take this class if you dont wanna have panic attacks all semester long because the work load is so high

professor durflinger was very demanding in this course. his expectations were way too high. the final was 15 pages and he only gave us a few days to write it. the term paper was impossible to get approved. he just kept declining topics for no reason. very very rude in emails. save yourself

Expect incredibly rude and unhelpful emails. This professor will deny your topic proposal repeatedly without providing any justification. If you ask him to elaborate as to why he rejected your proposal he'll likely respond with: "It's not my responsibility".

His lectures are really great and he clearly knows what he's talking about. Gives you the chance to explore topics with a range of themes and introduces facts and details you need. He'd be a good WW2 podcast host. The questions on exams are a little vague which can both give you room to interpret or fail, so be wary. He is tough on you for projects

Positive: His pre-recorded lectures are amazing. Negatives: This professor is incredibly rude in his emails. Youre going into the exam without knowing 80% of your grade. There are way too many lectures (+4hrs of content a week). The exam questions are vague (one of the final exam questions was: Why did the Allied lose the Second World War?).

By far the rudest and most unhelpful prof ive had my whole undergrad. He is not helpful at all, and posts far too much lecture content per week. He rejected atleast 10 of my topic proposals because they « were not good enough » but would never soecify why when asked.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: This might just be because of covid but the final exam is ridiculously long. You have 5 days to write a 7-page single-spaced essay with citations from the class readings (3500 words). Normally this doable but since its finals every other professor is assigning similar take-homes on the same week. Albeit, their papers are much smaller.

Certainly the worst professor I've ever had. Do NOT expect any help or forgiveness from this guy. I forgot to notify him about what I was writing about for the term paper and he refused to accept my paper once I submitted it.

This professor posts very monotonous lectures. doesn't follow the schedule of 2 per week; sometimes he'll post 3 or 4 and you just have to accept that? His emails are far from welcoming, and he is not helpful for the term paper. In addition, we are going into finals with only a grade worth 20% from the midterm; 80% of our grade is still unknown.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Lecture heavy', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: Really good lectures but omg is this guy rude and disrespectful in his emails. Very toxic.

A rude and condescending prof. His emails are SO rude and cold, and he is not very helpful when it comes to term paper help. I've never felt so unwelcomed in a class like I do in this one, as he talks down to students. He is very knowledgable however which is a good thing, but I would avoid at all costs

This professor's teaching style is monotonous at times. I understand we were in a pandemic during this class, but multiple 45+min slideshows with uninteresting delivery does not encourage me as a student to learn. Was very disrespectful and unprofessional when dealing with a late assignment. Not recommended.

In my 4 years of being a university student, I have never ever ever been more disrespected by a prof in my life. He's quite pretentious and thinks very highly of himself. I would highly recommend avoiding any class that he teaches if you can help it.
Very condescending and gives unnecessarily rude and snarky feedback on papers. Clearly thinks very highly of himself.

Extremely rude and a stickler for grammar. Tells you your essay outline is good and to proceed with it, then takes of grades for your essay needing more organization. Rude in emails and feedback. Not generally helpful.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'So many papers', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: I thought he was really scary at first, but he's actually really sweet and supportive. If you show an interest in the subject and a desire to do well, he will do everything he can to help you succeed. Fantastic lecturer, incredibly knowledgeable. Textbook is mandatory, but if you pay attention and put in the effort, you'll do fine. Recommended!

Durflinger is a great professor. He is incredibly knowledgeable on WW2. His lectures are packed full with info, but he is able to weave a simple narrative. Don't skip his class, because he doesn't post anything online. His assignments are straightforward. Fair grader. He's easy to access outside of class and ready to help a confused student.

He makes the class go by very quick due to the fact that his lectures are very interesting and he is really knowledgeable in the Second World War. He is persistent in helping students in their topic proposals and their essays to help them succeed. Highly recommend taking him

Mr. Durflinger is a very good and nice professor. He does have a superiority complex which makes the class unbearable at times. But he delivers great lectures which are content heavy and contain plenty of information. You need to attend class to pass. He doesn't use virtual campus to post his notes.

A very smart man but also very stuck up. Does not enjoy when students ask questions in class. Took 2 courses with him and had good grades but they require lots of work. VERY Condescending towards those he doesn't like. You learn lots but have to put up with his know it all attitude. Beware.

I've taken two of Derflinger's classes, World War 1 and 2. It was the same for both, if you do the readings and go to class you'll do well. I didn't do the readings for WW2 and got a C+, did them for WW1 and got a B+. As hard as he is, it's the only class I've ever taken where I didn't look at the clock once. If you like modern history, take them.

Great professor! Knows his stuff and makes lectures very interesting. I learned a lot in both his WWI and WWII class. Not a horribly tough marker but does make you work for it for sure. Do not expect to pass without going to class. He is always willing to give students help on assignments outside of class.  Recommend him!

Dr. Durflinger is an amazing lecturer! He is the kind of guy that can get you interested in even the smallest details of military history. Did not find him a particularly tough grader, I would say even more important than doing readings is just go to class. If you do, you will do well. Such a nice, knowledgeable guy.
A decent lecturer and good scholar with a god-complex.
Mean for meanness' sake; Thinks he is the only person that matters in the world; Very hard marker

I READ THE REVIEWS ON DURFLINGER PRIOR TO STARTING HIS CLASS AND I WAS EXPECTING IT TO BE VERY DIFFICULT. IT DID RECQUIRE ALOT OF WORK BUT IF YOU ATTEND ALL THE CLASSES AND DO THE READINGS IT IS EASY TO GET AN A

Fantastic lectures. Very engaging. Learn a fantastic amount about a wide range of material. Heavy textbook use. Lectures are absolutely mandatory to attend. Not an overly hard marker, but you cannot BS around him.
Is a bit all over the place. Not really interesting. Very boring when he talks. Makes 1:30 classes seem like 3hours classes ! Tough marker ! Very knowledgeable though.
Hard grader and beware - the readings are absolutely mandatory for both midterms and final exam.
Very interesting professor. Has good knowledge on canadian history. Hard grader,one big project but learned a lot!
The best.

Has a slightly twisted sense of humour, challenges standard ideas about Canadian history, and seems to bitterly hate Trudeau. All of which keeps the lectures interesting. Despite discovering that I don't like Canadian history, his course was still worth taking.

Fabulous professor. He's a hard marker with high standards, but he gives you what you deserve. Very helpful if you have questions about anything in his class. The discussion groups were enlightening, and we got good use out of the textbook. Finally, a professor who doesn't spare the details about the 20th cen wars. Would take again in a heartbeat.
Best prof I've had in 4 years at Ottawa U. Excellent speaker, really interesting to listen to and know what's he talking about. A++

I dont like him, its a first year class and the correction of the examns are terrible....if we dont cover 30 years with most of what happened he will give us a bad grade...he teach us like if we were 10 years old, his french is not that great and he always repeat the same thing.
Awesome prof. Very inspiring. I changed majors from crim to history because of him. Strongly recommend him. Gets a little behind toward the end though.

Loves his military history but makes it interesting for students more interested in social history. Great to talk to about essays etc. Stern about marks but you get what you deserve and learn TONS. Highly recommended for any history class
Très bon cours que je recommande à toutes et tous. Excellent professeur.

I loved him, Durflinger made everything really interesting and was straightforward and clear in his expectations.  Plus he always had a great attitude - wont take**** from students but is still a nice guy.
good prof, very very focus on the military aspect of history

I hated this class with a passion, if you are a french seperatist you might love it. He always goes off on tangents and makes the class very boring. there is a lot of reading, and his midterms were so broad the class avg was 50% on it. I hated this class. Id recomment Prof. Piva HE IS AWESOME!
Great, great, great!
Très bon cours.
Va trop en detail et en resultat n'as pas le temps de couvrir toute la matière importante.
Très gentil, très passionne par son metier.  Il explique très bien..même s'il rajoute plusieurs details inutiles...interessant par exemple...
